\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {\relax Figure\nobreakspace {\relax 1}.1}{\ignorespaces Schematic dependency graph for the Lean formalization effort around Fermat's Last Theorem. The intent is to visualize a theorem not as an isolated statement, but as the endpoint of a large directed dependency structure spanning multiple mathematical domains. Such a graph highlights why theorem proving, formal verification, and related activities may be viewed as allocation problems over interdependent tasks.}}{2}{figure.caption.2}%
